I"Í<p>I wanted an easy way to create my navigation menus and I found a great post <a href="http://www.tournemille.com/blog/How-to-create-data-driven-navigation-in-Jekyll/">here</a> on using the new-ish â€˜dataâ€™ feature of Jekyll.</p>

<p>What this allows us to do is centralize our navigation setup (pages and subpages) so any changes are kept out of our actual layout code.</p>

<p>Hereâ€™s what I did:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Add a new file called <code class="highlighter-rouge">nav.yml</code> in your _data directory
    <ul>
      <li>Create the _data directory if it doesnâ€™t already exist</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Paste this template into <code class="highlighter-rouge">_data/nav.yml</code> and edit it to fit your needs</li>
</ul>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>- title: "Home"
  href: "/"

- title: "Blog"
  href: "/blog/"

- title: "Misc"
  subcategories:
    - subtitle: "Example"
      subhref: "#"
    - subtitle: "Example2"
      subhref: "#"
</code></pre></div></div>

<ul>
  <li>Edit your <code class="highlighter-rouge">_includes/naviation.html</code> to match the following</li>
</ul>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>
&lt;nav class="animenu"&gt;	
  &lt;input type="checkbox" id="button"&gt;
  &lt;label for="button" onclick&gt;Menu&lt;/label&gt; 
  &lt;ul&gt;
    {% for nav in site.data.nav %}
      {% if nav.subcategories != null %}
	&lt;li&gt;
	  &lt;a href="{{ site.url }}{{ nav.url }}"&gt;{{ nav.title }} &amp;#x25BC;&lt;/a&gt;
	  &lt;ul&gt;
	    {% for subcategory in nav.subcategories %}
	      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="{{ site.url }}{{ subcategory.subhref }}"&gt;{{ subcategory.subtitle }}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	    {% endfor %}
	  &lt;/ul&gt;
	{% elsif nav.title == page.title %}
	  &lt;li class="active"&gt;&lt;a href="{{ nav.url }}"&gt;{{ nav.title }}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	{% else %} 
	&lt;li&gt;
	  &lt;a href="{{ site.url }}{{ nav.href }}"&gt;{{ nav.title }}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  &lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/nav&gt; 

</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Now any time you want to update your navigation just edit the <code class="highlighter-rouge">_data/nav.yml</code> file and rebuild your site.</p>
